105  void init_vars(const VariableList& target_vars) {
106 #ifndef NDEBUG
107  if (!target_vars.is_permutation(vars_)) {
108  if (TiledArray::get_default_world().rank() == 0) {
109  TA_USER_ERROR_MESSAGE(
110  "The array variable list is not compatible with the expected "
111  "output:"
112  << "\n expected = " << target_vars
113  << "\n array = " << vars_);
114  }
115 
116  TA_EXCEPTION(
117  "Target variable is not a permutation of the given array variable "
118  "list.");
119  }
120 #endif // NDEBUG
121  }

126  void init_vars() {}

128  void init_distribution(World* world,
129  const std::shared_ptr<pmap_interface>& pmap) {
130  ExprEngine_::init_distribution(world, (pmap ? pmap : array_.pmap()));
131  }

136  trange_type make_trange() const { return array_.trange(); }

160  dist_eval_type make_dist_eval() const {
161  // Define the distributed evaluator implementation type
162  typedef TiledArray::detail::ArrayEvalImpl<array_type, op_type, policy>
163  impl_type;
164 
166  std::shared_ptr<impl_type> pimpl = std::make_shared<impl_type>(
167  array_, *world_, trange_, shape_, pmap_, perm_, ExprEngine_::make_op());
168 
169  return dist_eval_type(pimpl);
